# RITUAL FOR CRYPTIC COUNCILS
# INTRODUCTORY REMARKS {{bookmark intro}}

The following are the officers of a Council of Cryptic Masons:
.editorial (See Fig. 1 for placement. * are defined as line officers)

%TABS 0.1in 0.25in 2.4in 2.55in
:   : [[list-caption]]Elective:[[/list-caption]] :   : [[list-caption]]Appointive:[[/list-caption]] :
: * : Illustrious Master                         : * : Conductor of the Council :
: * : Deputy Master                              : * : Steward :
: * : Principal Conductor of the Work            :   : Chaplain (optional) :
:   : Treasurer                                  :   : Marshal (optional) :
:   : Recorder                                   :   : Musician (optional) :
: * : Captain of the Guard                       :   : Sentinel  :
%TABS

Degrees may be conferred to great effect when the Council has a
full array of proper and well-fitted costumes available.  Please see
"Costumes for Degree Conferrals" on page 321 for more details.
{{endnote-ref costumes}}

The Council will also need a three-branched candelabra; at least six
trowels; shackles; three ancient squares; a Royal Arch Ark with
plate containing the cryptogram; the items from 1 Kings 7:48-50
and furnishings for S. S. so far as possible; a representation of the |
Nine Arches, Aaron's Rod, Pot of Manna, and the Book of the Law. <|

Councils of Royal Masters are "dedicated to Adoniram," and
Councils of Select Masters are "dedicated to our Three Ancient
Grand Masters."

A Candidate is "Introduced to the Rites and Honors of a Royal
Master" and "Chosen to Assist in the Building of the Secret Vault
as a Select Master."  A Candidate may also be "Greeted as a Super-
Excellent Master" (using a separately furnished ritual.)

Whether in full costume or standard attire, the I._M., or any Officer
or other Companion whose head is covered, may elect to uncover
whenever the signs are to be given.

R._M. salute is performed by giving the Sign alone.  S._M. salute is
performed by giving the Due-Guard and first two Penal Signs only.

%PAGE

## THE ALTAR

The Cryptic Degrees may be opened and conferred using either the
usual Symbolic Lodge altar, or the triangular altar of the Royal
Arch Chapter.

The Volume of the Sacred Law is open to 1 Kings 6:27 in the R._M.
Degree, and to Exodus 16:32-35 in the S._M. Degree.

While open on the Select Master Degree, the Sword and Trowel
may also be displayed upon the altar.  If used, the Trowel should be
positioned first, with its tip facing west.  It is then overlaid by the
Sword with its point facing north.  These should be put into place
before opening ceremonies begin.

The size and shape of the individual Altar and Great Lights in a
particular Council may necessitate variations in placement, but the
important quality is that the Sword and Trowel do not interfere in
any way with the placement of the Volume of the Sacred Law, or
the Square & Compasses, and shall not interfere with the placement
of the hands of a candidate while receiving the obligation. {{bookmark altar-placement}}

