## OFFICER'S JEWELS | For a Council of Crypic Masons

%SPACE
%IMAGE "figures/02-officer-jewels.png" 33

%PAGE chapter

# COUNCIL OF CRYPTIC MASONS
# OFFICER'S JEWELS {{bookmark jewels}}

Each Officer's Jewel of the Cryptic Council is situated within or
overlaid upon a perfect equilateral triangle.  These Jewels may be
suspended from purple collars, or affixed to the left breast pocket
of a jacket, and should also be depicted upon the body of the Apron
assigned to the Office.  (See Fig. 2)

%TABS 0 3in:dot:right
: Illustrious Master                         : Square & Trowel :
: Deputy Master           : Level surmounted by Crown & Trowel :
: Pr. Cond. of the Work  : Plumb surmounted by Turban & Trowel :
: Treasurer                            : Crossed Keys & Trowel :
: Recorder                           : Crossed Quills & Trowel :
: Captain of the Guard                   : Battle Axe & Trowel :
: Marshal (Optional)                 : Crossed Batons & Trowel :
: Conductor of the Council         : Parchment Scroll & Trowel :
: Steward                            : Crossed Sabers & Trowel :
: Chaplain (Optional)      : Volume of the Sacred Law & Trowel :
: Musician (Optional)                          : Lyre & Trowel :
: Sentinel    : Crossed Long Swords (or Single Sword) & Trowel :
%TABS

|24|
## POSITION OF ATTENTION {{bookmark attention}}

Standing, body erect, with arms and hands in a relaxed position at
the sides, the chin up, and eyes looking ahead.

|32|
## POSITION OF REVERENCE

During prayer, and while the Conductor of the Council is attending
to the Great Lights at the altar, other Companions should have
heads bowed, arms crossed upon the chest, left over right, both
hands visible.

