: ~  : Sound of e             : @ : ing :
: >> : esses                  : [[underline]]w[[/underline]] : were :
: ^  : ese                    : - :  and (spaced "_-_" not like d-g) :

# KEY TO ALTERNATE READINGS | FOR MULTIPLE CANDIDATES

.rubric There are many passages in the Cryptic ritual that have an
  alternate reading depending on whether a degree is being
  conferred upon only one candidate or multiple candidates
  at the same time.  These readings are most likely self explanatory,
  but in case of any question, here is the rule:

.rubric When two words are given in braces separated by a slash, such
  as "{him/them}" the first word is used for a single candidate,
  and the second word is used for multiple candidates.  Words or
  letters given in parenthesis, such as the "(s)" in the word
  "companion(s)" are to be spoken for multiple candidates only,
  and words or letters given in brackets, such as "[a]" are to be
  spoken for a single candidate only.  Here is an example as it is
  written in the text:

|27|
%ROLE sample "Sample–"

sample: Retire to the preparation room with companion(s) A, B,
  C, and D, clothe {him/them} as [a] Fellowcraft
  Mason(s), return and present {his/their} work for
  inspection.

.rubric For a single candidate, the above should be read as follows:

|34|
sample: Retire to the preparation room with companion A, clothe
  him as a Fellowcraft Mason, return and present his work
  for inspection.

.rubric For multiple candidates, the sample should be read as follows:

|40|
sample: Retire to the preparation room with companions A, B, C,
  and D, clothe them as Fellowcraft Masons, return an
  present their work for inspection.
%END-PAGE
